Class FilterByFieldQueryParam

public class FilterByFieldQueryParam
extends FilterQueryParam

This is a query param class provides the ability to submit filter by field searches with a VdrSearchExpression search expression that contains search terms joined by either AND or OR search conjunction operators.

The constructors of this class verify that the search terms submitted contain operators acceptable for this query. These operators are:

  • Contains (CT)
  • Equals (EQ)
  • Not Equals (NE)
  • Less Than (LT)
  • Less Than or Equal To (LE)
  • Greater Than (GT
  • Greater Than or Equal To (GE)
An OperatorNotSupportedException exception will be thrown if an ineligible operator is found within a search expression's search terms. A ParsingException exception will be thrown if invalid search term is found in the search Expression

Search Example:

("ACCOUNT" GreaterThan "1003") AND ("DEPT" Equals "Sales")

Create Filter by Field Search Terms

FilterTerm term1 = new FilterTerm( "ACCOUNT", ComparisonOperators.GT ,"1003");
FilterTerm term2 = new FilterTerm("DEPT", ComparisonOperators.EQ ,"Sales");

Create a Search Expression (joined by AND)

VdrSearchExpression SearchExpr = VdrSearchExpression.createAndExpression();
SearchExpr.addTerm(term1);
SearchExpr.addTerm(term2);

Create an FilterByFieldQueryParam

QueryParam qParam = new FilterByFieldQueryParam(reportID, versionList, SearchExpr);

Create instance of FilterFactory

FilterFactory filter = session.createListFactory(SessionFactoryType.Filter);
Submit the query

INode[] enodes = filter.createList(qParam);
